  "title": "PROJECT MANAGER / SITE MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>We are a well-established construction company with an enviable track record in major civil engineering and building works. To meet our continuing growth, we require suitably qualified candidates for the following position:</p>\n<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Able to coordinate with consultants, sub-contractors, and relevant authorities</li>\n  <li>Able to handle all trades of works on-site (ie structural works, architectural works, building works, M&amp;E works, interior fitting-out works)</li>\n  <li>Set up and maintain project control system, planning, work schedules, and monitoring of project costing, work progress, and coordination with all parties involved to ensure work progress smoothly &amp; completed with target time and budget</li>\n  <li>Review and provide project-related correspondence including progress reports, proposals, requirements documentation, and presentations.</li>\n  <li>Manage defects’ rectification and improvement works of completed projects</li>\n  <li>Implement various quality, safety, and environmental management systems</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum of 5 year’s experience in projects and site management in the local construction industry.</li>\n  <li>Shall be able to manage and lead the Projects Team and have proven experience in construction projects planning</li>\n  <li>Strong in IT-based project management software such as MS Projects &amp; Excel.</li>\n  <li>Prefer with R&amp;R / Town Council project experience</li>\n  <li>Only Singaporean and PR. Must possess a relevant degree in Building or Engineering.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Competitive remuneration package commensurate with qualifications will be offered.</strong></p>\n<p>Interested candidates are invited to apply via email with an updated resume, which should include current and expected salaries, date of availability, and a recent photograph in MS Word Format. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>Thank you for applying.</p>",
